cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the robustness of neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a gradient-based method to craft adversarial examples, which involves optimization techniques and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of noisy data, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) or neural networks (cs.NE).
